content: How good is this app? Well, when I see somebody mixing with an iPad, I actually feel sorry for them. This app has been my go to platform for nearly three years of gigs ranging from simple guitar/vocal setups to running FOH and 6 monitor mixes for multi-band festivals. So, speaking from experience, I would choose this app over the Apple platform for any ONE of the following reasons: 1 - Build Quality. It is fast, responsive and reliable to a fault. It just WORKS, no matter what I throw at it. 2 - Cost of Implementation. For the cost of a single iPad, I can buy three 10 inch tablets whose specs are more than sufficient to run this app in a manner best described as effortless. 3 - Efficiency of Use. You can literally create your own custom layout, giving immediate, top-layer access to every channel strip and control that is actually relevant to the gig at hand. 4 - Responsiveness of the Developer. Log on to the Behringer user forum and you'll see what I mean.

This app works just as described. And I like the fact that works on my phone. So far works better than the iPad app. Can you make an app or an add on, in which I can save a scene and save it in the phone and edit it offline. Well worth it

This app is 10 times better than its counter part iOS version, because it allow you to customize your screen layers therefore you can customize your workflow.  The IOS version has one flaw in controlling the mix the main L/R fader is not in the same page of the DCA's.  With this Android version, I can put DCA and Main L/R controls at any pages.  I can flip thru any layers, ie.e  bus , FX, aux, or channels and DCA + L/R are always at my finger tips.  There are some other functions that I need to know to how to use and to customize but I need a manual.
Easier to use than the factory app.  Love the ability to customize layers! Now if I could only figure out how to get a tap tempo on the layer....

This app is very useful. I can control my X32 Rack using my tablet & in some ways it's easier to use than the official X32 Edit on PC. Sure it doesn't look as "glossy" as the iPad version, but the functionality is all there (and then some) and on my Note Pro 12.2 it's a complete touch-sensitive control surface. Well worth the donation!
Very well written Android app for the X32 mixer that has features that even the Behringer app doesn't have.

Makes Beringer app seem a little clunky. So we'll thought out that it's a breeze to use on your phone. After using the free version for a while I bought the donate version because the developer deserves it!

Yamaha needs to take a few cues from this....oh wait I think they did recently. However, the iOS Yamaha app uses the internal microphone for the RTA not data from the console! I love this app and the time the dev has spent making such a refined product. Now if you had a Yamaha version I would buy it too! Thank you for supporting us android users with a behringer console. Love the added features in the donate version. Well worth it!
Gets all 5 from me. You could not ask for a better app.
Great job.
Best mixing app I've seen by far.
Better than Behringer's app!
Works flawless and irreplaceable  in my x32 rack setup.  Would like to see some gui skins on the fx settings though.
Worth every penny.  New features are great.

Everything I heard/read about this app is true. Excellent visualizations and customizable workflow. One warning though. If you get a new Nexus 7 to run it on make sure to do all of the OS upgrades  (a total of seven in my case) or else the app may crash until you do.

This app just gets better and better! This app is worth donating for. To get the features included in this control app for another name brand digital console costs 149$ and the access is still limited and you have to run a PC as a server to get android connectivity. Buy it.. Its a total no brainer!!
Awesome, ran sound system from organ, when sound person was out one Sunday. .
Much much better than stock apps. Use Andy to port on PC!
Amazing App.
Works great love it simple and easy to use prefer android over apple anyday
This app works with behringer x32, while the actual app for the system doesn't ( on my phone and tablet, their app keeps crashing)  Plus, this app looks better.

Mixing station is the best remote mixing app ive ever seen. None of others come even close. Only thing i would like to see added is some kind of custom fader that can control any parameter i specify, for example channel 14 send to fx3.

This app is awesome. I was happy to donate even though the beta was fine. Functions flawlessly. Everything is easy to access. Even if I'm the room with the board I'll still use it to access most settings.
This is my first app that I ever bought on Google Play, and it is deserve it. 5 stars!
Fantastic app! Makes whole room mixing not only possible, but easy :-)
Live it! Used for monitor mixing.
Great app.   Gets better with continued development
Stable connection to X32. Has everything you need for mixing from Android. Updated frequently.
Donated for this and I'm very happy. Full control and very user friendly.
So much better than Behringers own app.  I bought an Android tablet just to have access to this app to control the X32 compact at my church.
Pretty amazing my friend! I would go as far as saying this app actually adds value to the X32 over competitors!! No joke
This app has way more features than the original behringer app, and you can see the Smart ART Graph in real time !!    but for a mini smart phone its too cluttered

I'd like the tool very much. One request though, can you add the scene files loading from the tablet and apply to the console? This feature is available on Win & Linux version and is helpful to edit the mix offline. Thanks.
replyContent:
Hi,
Thanks!
The ability to save/load offline scenes is quite complex and I'm not 100% sure if I will add it anytime soon, but it's on my todo list!

content: Top notch app, easy to operate and customize to my needs, AND the developer was responsive almost immediately, when I had a feature request, last summer. Considering the size of the investment in the mixer, donating is a small price to pay, for all this well orchestrated functionality.
Nothing else comes close.  This program is amazing.
Better than the official Behringer app.
This app works fantastic
I only own iPads because they control my X32s.  This app is awesome and I can now get rid of them!
Latest update brought some of the last things that were missing. Channelstrip "pages" really speeds up setting up. Thanks for another great update!
This app is superior to the iPad version and Behringers official app. Pay a few $$$ and its well worth it.
App is great and easy to use.  David is doing an excellent job on this one!

I use this, Android version, in tandem with the oem ios controller for a number of shows.  While I feel that the faders seem more responsive in ios oem, behringer has failed to integrate user assignable function, or cue recall, thus making mix station an invaluable addition!
Can i use this app on a microsoft Surface Pro??
replyContent:
Hi,
With an android emulator it should work.

content: Picasso APP the best for the X32

I reviewed the free app, just wanted to give you 5 stars again! Thanks again for making such a great app! ... EDIT - this app just keeps getting better and better. I can't say enough how much I love using it. You're doing great work!
Posted my main review on the free version, had to buy the donate version to support the developer. Keep up the good work!

This application is awesome. Behringer should pay this guy for making a product that's better than their own. You can control everything with this application. Love being able to walk around with my phone and adusting the FOH sound as well as monitor mixes. Totally awesome work. Please donate so this application can continue to be developed in thr future.
Awesome...ok awesome Again

Yeah, this is an amazing app.  Thanks for developing this.  I use regularly at my church.  Makes it far easier to adjust the FOH mix, monitors, Narthex, hallways, other rooms etc., from wherever I happen to be!  I am used this on Android 5.0 and am now on 5.0.1 with no problem at all!  Thanks again for your work!
Great app I donated to him after using the free app ! So easy to use

Behringer's app for android device only allows adjustments to monitors. This app allows all adjustments including eq. Like many churches our sound booth is in the worst possible location for proper mixing. This app allows you to adjust the mix in the best locations in the building. Well worth downloading the donate app. Thanks for offering this app.
Great for when you want to walk the room and adjust front of house from that trouble spot. Nice to be able to mute a channel from the stage as you reconfigure the layout mid-rehearsal.
Love it.
Really great so, pleasure use and responsive developer.
from hand signals to the sound engineer when my in-ear monitor mix needs adjusting!
I love having an option for android.
Like the customizable layouts. Soild.
Is causeing WiFi to turn off and won't connect to 2.08 firmware help please
replyContent: Hi, send me an email with a detailed error description: david at dev-core.org

content: Use it every week for services!

Have been using this for months now.  Touching the actual board is a thing of the past with your app!  Best feature is selecting the order of how the channels are displayed. Keep up the awesome developments!

Makes using the X32 series easier. I especially like leaving the RTA display up on one tablet while driving specific aspects of a mix with another.  I also like giving the video crew their own mix and provide them a tablet so they can tailor it to their liking.
Excellent work on this. Thanks!
Well worth the price, bug fixes and new features added regularly, keep up the good work Dave

This application works like a charm. The hardware it controls is very nice, but only has an ipad app, now David has blessed us with this Android app and I'm loving it. I do sound in church (now for ~25 years) and the introduction of the Behringer x32 system in combination with this app makes life so much easier!
The best keeps getting better. Awesome app. Well worth the money. The RTA is awesome!
Better than the official app
Most amazing app, and it just keeps getting better. Thank you for your hard work!
I forgot my ipad running a show,  Oh what's this? My phone runs the show.. What's also sick,  is the RTA is there!  Love this app!
I love this app. Maybe improve by making naming channels easier. If you hit enter, you go to the next channel?
replyContent: Good idea! I added it onto my list

content: Has many pluses and I love using it in conjunction with an iPad and a PC.  ;-)

Awesome mixing app. Works perfectly for FOH mixing, personal monitor mixing on stage, and anything else you'd really need to do on the X32. Great work! Thanks so much!  Loving the new update and UI options.
Very happy to be able to compensate this guy for doing the work behringer didn't. Every issue I've had has been resolved and the developer is one of the most helpful dudes on the planet.
replyContent:
Tap delay should be working. Or did I forgot some FX?

david@dev-core.org

content: Brilliant piece of software use it all the time.
It's very intuitive and easy to use.
Great
This app does everything it should and the developer works tirelessly to release new features and improvements. Worth every penny and more!  Great work David.

Almost perfect app. I tried the beta version and was so impressed I paid for this. works great on my X32 I can sit at the other end of my studio and conrol my mixer easily whil sat at my keyboards.. simple uncluttered design..intuitive.. and like someone else said, its somewhat easier than using the desk itself lol. and the matrix function is worth the asking price alone. thanks developers!

Love the app! The developer is always on top of improvements. One wish I've had is that we could swipe between faders instead of having to switch banks. It would really help. Still a great app though!
I use this at every service.  In some ways it's easier than the actual board.  Great job.

Works pretty good.  In fact I went ahead and donated because I very much appreciate the hard work that the developer puts in. Every concern I've had has been addressed by the programmer personally.  Gotta love this guy!  If you use this you should DONATE!
replyContent:
Which FX do you need to control with the custom buttons?
david[at]dev-core.org

content: Thank you so much for filling a need. I was dreading having to get an iPad just to control the x32. This single developer has done what a company either would not do or did not see as necessary to do. I hope they are paying you.
Galaxy Note 3 crashes repeatedly is trying ro reconnect to console... would love for this to be fixed...
Its great that an indie dev has taken the time to service android users in the pro audio field. Too often equipment makers neglect this OS even though it runs on more devices than any other.
No downside, nailed it.

I've been using free version for a while comparing withe the iPad oficial version and this is simply better in all aspects. Better organized, easy navigation, faster response, can see the RTA live as well as live operation of the gate and dynamics graph of the console. I just donated. Is more functional and becoming better with each update. Thanks and continue with your development
Great app works flawlessly. I recommend this app. I don't have to wave for the sound engineers to turn up something.
Works hard to make our androids control our x32 decks.  Thanks!

I can't say enough about this app and developer. The app works exactly as it should. As an Android user I'd be completely out of luck if it weren't for David and his app. I don't really understand how Behringer could be so short sighted, assuming perhaps that only Apple users could be creative. Well, no loss. This is actually better than the app Behringer put out for i-products. The developer is VERY responsive to users' suggestions or questions. He's the best!
I definitely recommend this app
I like using the Android mixing station app as much as I like using the IOS X32 mixing app if not more.
Works great, does everything I need it to do. Amazing to be able to control my own mix from on-stage without having to flag down the sound man

Controls our church's Behringer x32 flawlessly! When Behringer made an update for the board, everyone lost the ability to control the board by tablet except those with this app. It kept working perfectly the entire time. Can't believe the number of improvements in the program over the last few years on the free version. Wanted to donate the money because I'm so grateful for you making and updating this program! It rocks and so do you!

Excellent app. I am using this with a 7 inch tablet. I especially love the touchscreen eq with RTA overlay. I also love being able to use sends on fader to change between mixes. Thanks to David for making this possible on Android.

Use it every week for church I even have some apple guys liking this set up better then theirs.. You are the man :-)  although recently it has been playing up when I turn the screen off it dc from the desk then have to reconnect each time... I have a note 3
Great app, more than happy to pay for it for what it does, keep up the excelent work David
One of the few apps worth buying. Keep up the good work.
This is really a great asset to our mixing team,  keep up the good work,  very happy to support your time and investment in making it so easy. Great job.

Gladly donate to help develop the app. I use it quite regularly on a Nexus 7 and it works flawlessly. Soon to be using with just the x32 rack and tablet as I'm happy with the stability and ease of use.
Outdoing Behringer daily!
Anyone who uses this board should have app!
No problem paying for this as +Behringer needs to catch up on the  android side. Please keep up the good work.

I love being able to use my droid to control the x32. This app has just as many features as the iPad app, and there's no need to purchase expensive apple hardware! Full control over any wireless network hooked up to the x32. Definitely worth the donation price!

Awesome app!  Love the ease of use, flexible setup options, rapid bug fixing, and most importantly the "smoothness" when adjusting parameters. The fine vs regular setting for the faders is a great touch. Keep up the great work!!
Been waiting a long time
Just take my money, take it!
Excellent.  So glad I found your app.  Did the donate version and yet still asks for me to donate.  Curious.
replyContent: That's a bug when both versions are installed on one device. It will be fixed with the next update :-)

content: Awesome app I believe you are doing great things with this I will support you. So I did buy the donate version. Keep up the good work
Well worth paying for the great work the developer has done with this app.
Everything about this app is great. It really extends the x32 and allows me to get the full potential out of my console. Everyone that uses this app should support the developer!
